snippet.title: WASHI YO WASHI - They Call Him OG | Pawan Kalyan | Emraan Hashmi | Sujeeth | Thaman S | Dvv Danayya
snippet.description:
The wait is worth it ‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüî•

#WashiYoWashi in the thunderous voice of Pawan Kalyan üí•

#OG #TheyCallHimOG

Music : Thaman S
Singer - Pawan Kalyan 

Programmed & arranged by - thaman S 
Song Programmed by - Roshan Vishal
NAKODA & Japanese drums - Sivamani 
Additional TAIKOS & Hokkaido drums - - Beyond Sound (T) 
Vocal Supervision - Thaman S & Sujeeth

Recorded by - Thaman S @ Vibe ( HYD )

Mix and Mastered by Shadab Rayeen @ New Edge ( Mumbai )
Assistant engineers - Jazbaat, Sohamm, Prasad

Musicians Co Ordinator - Manikandan K
Studio Manager - Seenu & Sridhar
Studio Assistance - Raju, Kannan, Lingam & Pawan

Cast - Pawan Kalyan, Emraan Hashmi, Priyanka Arul Mohan, Arjun Das, Sriya Reddy, Prakash Raj

Movie Name: They Call Him OG
Written & Directed by Sujeeth
Music by Thaman S
Production: DVV Entertainment
Presented by: Smt D.Parvathi
Produced by DVV Danayya, Kalyan Dasari
Cinematographers : Ravi K Chandran (ISC), Manoj Paramahamsa (ISC)
Production Designer : AS Prakash
Editor: Navin Nooli
Costume Designers: Darshan Jalan & Neelanchal Kumar Ghosh
Creative Director : Ashwin Mani
Creative Producer : Harish Pai
Action Masters : A Vijay, Peter Hein, Dhilip Subbarayan, Kevin Kumar, Stunt Silva, Sunil Rodrigues, Kecha Khampakdee, Juji, Supreme Sundar, Jashwa, Parvez
Co-director: Somaraju PVV
Direction Department : Uday Alla, Aarun Thevar, Lokesh Srinivasan, Kishore Sarella,
Kedar Pashikanti, Durga D.R, Sainadh Alla, Mithilesh Sivagani, Rithica Devireddy,
I.Chaitanya Sravanth, N.Sruti Ranjani, RSN.Roshan Sharif
Chief Associate Editors : Raam tumu, Srinu Bainaboyina
Associate Editors: Prashanth Tej, Yogi (D.F.Tech), Vishnu ramagiri
Executive Producer: Sathyanarayana Guggilla
Production Controller: Manikanta Rongala
Sound Design : Sync Cinema
VFX Supervisor : Raghav Tammareddy
Stills : Mallesh Thatha
Marketing: Walls and Trends
PRO: Venugopal
DI : Annapurna Studios
Marketing : Walls & Trends
Video composition: Walls & Trends
Lyrics -
WASHI YO WASHI 
EAGLE OH EAGLE 

Yasei no washi o korosu ni wa 
To kill a wild Eagle 

Mazu tsubasa o kiri otosu hitsu yoo ga aru 
You need to cut its wings first 

Jimen ni ochitara..me o eguri dasu 
When it falls on the ground you pluck its eyes 

Me ga mienaku nari, doko ni ikeba ii no ka wakara naku suru 
It becomes blind and doesn‚Äôt know where to go 

Sokode ashi o kitte ugokenaku suru 
That‚Äôs when you cut its legs and make it immobile 

Soshite, yasei no shinzou o eguri dasu noda 
And that‚Äôs when you will pluck its wild heart out 

WASHI YO WASHI 
EAGLE O EAGLE

snippet.title: Nallaru Po | Dude | Pradeep Ranganathan | @SaiAbhyankkar | Tippu | Mohit Chauhan | Keerthiswaran
snippet.description:
Presenting the Lyrical Video song of 'Nallaru po' from 'Dude', Written & Directed by Keerthiswaran featuring Pradeep Ranganathan, Mamitha Baiju, R.Sarath Kumar, Hridhu Haroon,Rohini, Aishwarya sharma, Dravid selvam & Others.

An @SaiAbhyankkar  Musical 
Song Title: 'Nallaru po'
Album: Dude

Music Credits:

Composed and produced by @SaiAbhyankkar 
Singers: Tipu , @SaiAbhyankkar  & Mohit Chauhan
Lyricist : Vivek 
Synth ,keys and Bass programmed by @SaiAbhyankkar 
Acoustic ,Electric Bass Guitar & Charango - Keba 
Navtar - Vishnu Ramprasad 
Violin - Chinmayi 
Live Rhythm - Yanka Rhythm group 
Rhythm produced by @SaiAbhyankkar 

Music Supervisor : Sachin Lal
Music consultant : Adesh krishna 
All recorded and produced at Yolo rechords , engineered by Rajesh Kannan 
Mixed & Masterd by @SaiAbhyankkar 

Movie Credits:

Banner: Mythri Movie Makers
Writer & Director: Keerthiswaran
Producers: Naveen Yerneni, Y Ravi shankar
CO-Producer:  Anil Yerneni

Art Director: P.L. Subenthar   
VFX supervisors: Ramkumar sundaram 
DI & VFX: Mango post
Colorist: Suresh ravi 
Sound Design: Sync Cinema
Sound Mix: Rajakrishnan M.R
Direction team: Krish Chidambaram, K.C. Perumal, Anirudh Ramesh, Tamilselvan Sankar, Karthick Sekar, Giriprasath, N. Nagaraj

PRO: Suresh Chandra, Sathish S2Media
Production Controllers : Rangaraj Perumal, E. Suresh Nambiraj
Marketing: First Show
Lyric Video: ADFX


Lyrics:

Nee ketaa unna kooda un kaiyil vittu poguren
Aasa pola vaazhndhukkoyen po
Un mela kaadhal vachene
Thothadhaalum theerala
Ponadhaalum maarala 

Nee ketaa unna kooda un kaiyil vittu poguren
Aasa pola vaazhndhukko di po
Ennalum Kaadhal kuthadhu 
Parvayal Yenga Vechaale 

Paakaama pesaama seraama ponaalum 
Ennaalum nallaru po 
Hey thaangaama thoongaama naan inga vaazhndhaalum
Neeyaachum nallaaru po
 
Kaadhalaa en nenjam
Yekkamaa aanan naane
Kaayamaa nee senjum
Sirikkirene
Yaaradi kutham solla 
En vidhi  enna kolla 
Nee vantha nenjukkulla  
Ippothu onnumilla 

Veroru kayyoda un veral paathen naane 
Vegura nenjoda pogurene
Nethu un kannil naane
Innaikku yaaro dhaane 
Thindaadurene maane
Thaa po nu vittutene 

Paakaama pesaama enkuda seraama ponaalum nallaru po 
Hey thaangaama thoongaama naan inga vaazhndhaalum 
Neeyaachum nallaarupo 

Hey Innoruthanoda nee poga 
Ullolachaloda naan poga 
Enna panna poren Thikku theriyaadhe 
Aanaa neeyum po
 
Hey Ennapanna poren kekaadha
Indha pakkam neeyum paakaadha
Michamulla kaadhal atchadhaya podum 
Nallaa vaazhu po

Hey thaangaama thoongaama naan inga vaazhndhaalum 
Neeyaachum nallaarupo 

Hey Innoruthanoda nee poga 
Ullolachaloda naan poga 
Enna panna poren Thikku theriyaadhe 
Aanaa neeyum po
 
Hey Ennapanna poren kekaadha
Indha pakkam neeyum paakaadha
Michamulla kaadhal atchadhaya podum 
Nallaa vaazhu po

snippet.title: India vs Pakistan, 14th T20 Match Cricket Live Commentary | IND Vs PAK Asia Cup 2025 | IND BAT
snippet.description:
India vs Pakistan, 14th T20 Match Cricket Live Commentary | IND Vs PAK Asia Cup 2025 | Live Match, IND BAT

For Contact umerhafeez2022@gmail.com 

Topics to be covered in the live stream üëáüèªüëáüèªüëáüèªüëáüèª

India vs Pakistan live Match
IND vs PAK live
IND vs PAK live match today 
Live Cricket Match Today 
Cricket Live 
Asia Cup Live 
Asia Cup 2025 Live
Live Match 

When: September 21, 06:30 PM LOCAL / 8:00 PM IST

Venue üëáüèª
India vs Pakistan live Match Dubai,
Where: Dubai International Stadium

What to expect: India vs Pakistan Asia Cup 2025, 14th Match. Earlier the 6th match of the Asia Cup was played between Pakistan vs India, India won by 7 wickets against Pakistan. If we look at pitch, another slow, dry surface, with equal boundaries on both sides and a thin grass cover to hold it together. It's likely the same center pitch used for the last India-Pakistan game. Suryakumar believes conditions here haven't shifted much across innings, unlike in Abu Dhabi where dew played a hand. Toss hasn't had a decisive say at this venue. The temperatures are forecast to be around 35 degrees around match start but the evenings in the city are already cooler than a week ago.

Team news:

India

After giving all batters and part-timers a run against Oman, India are set to revert to full strength, bringing back Jasprit Bumrah and Varun Chakaravarthy. Varun was among the few to train on match eve, practicing his scrambled seam legbreaks and googlies against a set of stumps. The others at the training were Shubman Gill and Abhishek Sharma, who bowled and batted and will be a key figure once again.

Injuries/Unavailability: Axar Patel, who struck his head while fielding in Abu Dhabi, is understood to be fine and available. No cover has been called.

Tactics & matchups: Samson and Tilak struggled against spin in Abu Dhabi, going 22 balls without a boundary. Their face-off with Abrar Ahmed will be crucial. The legspinner has bowled 70 balls in this Asia Cup and conceded just two boundaries.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav(c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson(w), Shivam Dube, Hardik Pandya, Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, Varun Chakaravarthy

Pakistan

Against UAE, Pakistan recalled Haris Rauf and Khushdil Shah, leaving out Sufiyan Muqeem and Faheem Ashraf. That balance is expected to continue. Eyes will be on Saim Ayub, on a hat-trick of ducks, and Hasan Nawaz, who needs runs.

Injuries/Unavailability: No reported injuries since their last match.

Tactics & matchups: Kuldeep Yadav's record against Pakistan looms again. Fakhar Zaman (30 runs, 3 dismissals in 35 balls) and Salman Agha (6 runs, 2 dismissals in 12 balls) have both found him tough across formats.

Probable XI: Saim Ayub, Sahibzada Farhan, Mohammad Haris(w), Fakhar Zaman, Salman Agha(c), Khushdil Shah, Hasan Nawaz, Mohammad Nawaz, Shaheen Afridi, Haris Rauf, Abrar Ahmed

snippet.title: Vrusshabha Official Teaser | Mohanlal as a King | Directed by Nanda Kishore | Diwali 2025 Release
snippet.description:
#Vrusshabha #Mohanlal #Diwali2025 #VrusshabhaTeaser #RoarOfVrusshabha #ConnekktMedia #BalajiTelefilms #AbishekSVyasStudios #AashirvadCinemas

Welcome to the World of Vrusshabha.

A unique story brought to life through an unforgettable cinematic experience for global audiences. With Mohanlal playing a king for the very first time in a bilingual epic, Vrusshabha is a film that promises to stay with you long after you leave the theatre. Vrusshabha is a grand Pan Indian film shot simultaneously in Malayalam and Telugu, and dubbed in Hindi and Kannada.


Starring: Mohanlal, Samarjit Lankesh, Ragini Dwivedi

Crew:
Written and Directed by Nanda Kishore & Team

Presented by Connekkt Media and Balaji Telefilms in association with Abishek S Vyas Studios,

LANGUAGE PYAR KI [Tu Machli Me Pani Barga] Sandeep Surila | Arvind Jangid | Sakshi | Haryanvi Song

Dive into the vibrant world of Sandeep Surila‚Äôs latest release ‚Äî ‚ÄúLanguage Pyar Ki‚Äù! With its catchy beats Gaur Beats and heartfelt lyrics Nikka Swami, this sensational Haryanvi-Romantic track celebrates love in every dialect.

#newharyanvisongsharyanavi2025 #sandeepsurila #arvindjangid   

Title - Language Pyar Ki
Starring - Arvind Jangid / Sakshi Dalal
Singer / Composer - Sandeep Surila
Lyrics - Nikka Swami
Music - Gaur Beat (Vinu Gaur - 9812110546)
Mix & Master - Sunil Balhara
DOP - Virender Punia
Make Up - Rahul Sain
Digital - Raj Gurjar (Rhythm Tune)
Management - Sameer Jangra
AD - Akash Puhal

Lyrics in English :-

Plus two cross margi re margi
Hogi tu thodi shararti shararti 
Ye mand mand bole ankhiyan ankhiyan 
Ye bole language pyar ki pyar ki
Yo gora gora rang Tera bawala sa dhang tera
Chori chori baat kare chhori ang ang tera

Tu ban than leher di firre re firre
Re hawa sare Saher ki firre re firre
Tu machali main paani barga
Oye dil ke mei tairti fire
Feeling ki tu chaide taar si taar si 
Re Hogi tu thodi shararti shararti 
Ye mand mand bole ankhiyan ankhiyan 
Ye bole language pyar ki pyar ki
+2 cross margi re margi
Hogi tu thodi shararti shararti 
Ye mand mand bole ankhiyan ankhiyan 
Ye bole language pyar ki pyar ki

Lipistic fiki lip pe lip pe
Re kala till gore chik pe chik pe 
Tu God ne banai gor te gor te 
Ye suit saree lage fit se fit se
Tu Balan ne firre sanwarti sanwarti 
Re Hogi tu thodi shararti shararti 
Ye mand mand bole ankhiyan ankhiyan 
Ye bole language pyar ki pyar ki
+2 cross margi re margi
Hogi tu thodi shararti shararti 
Ye mand mand bole ankhiyan ankhiyan 
Ye bole language pyar ki pyar ki

snippet.title: Live: IND vs PAK, Asia Cup 2025, Live Cricket Match Today, Cricket Live, India vs Pakistan Live
snippet.description:
Live: IND vs PAK, Asia Cup 2025, Live Cricket Match Today, Cricket Live, India vs Pakistan Live

For queries, you can email us at: mohsinali51066@gmail.com

1ST INNINGS PREVIEW:
Brilliant batting from Pakistan and equally bad fielding display from India, see the Men in Green post a formidable total of 171/5 in 20 overs after being sent in. Sahibzada Farhan was dropped by Abhishek Sharama in the first over and he didn't look back after that, taking on every bowler and smashing the ball to all parts of the Dubai International Stadium. A last ball six from Faheem Ashraf gives Pakistan the momentum at the halfway mark in this contest. This is also Pakistan's highest total against India batting first. The last time they crossed the 150-mark was back in 2022 at the MCG.

Earlier in the game, India won the toss and invited Pakistan to bat first under hot and humid conditions in Dubai. The Men in Green went with a changed opening pair as Fakhar Zaman replaced Saim Ayub to partner Sahibzada Farhan.

Abhishek Sharma dropped Farhan when he was on nought and he made India pay big time, scoring a quick-fire half-century. 

The opening pair put the pressure straightaway on Jasprit Bumrah and went after him from the word go. Hardik Pandya broke the opening stand by sending back Fakhar with an off-cutter.

Saim Ayub walked in at 3 and gave Farhan nice company as the duo kept the scoreboard ticking and put the bad balls away. They added 72 runs for the second wicket before Ayub fell for 21.

Farhan perished for 58. Mohammad Nawaz then took the onus on himself to move the scoreboard. Captain Salman Ali Agha remained not out on 17 off 13 but the cameo from Faheem Ashraf, who made 20 off 8 took Pakistan past the 170-run mark.

Bumrah was off colour tonight, he gave away 45 runs and failed to pick any wickets in his four overs. Shivam Dube was the unlikely hero with the ball for India, bowling four overs. He went for 33 and picked up 2 wickets. Kuldeep Yadav and Hardik Pandya were the other bowlers who got a wicket.

Mahalaya, signifies the termination of Pitri Paksha and the beginning of Devi Paksha, thus ushering in the season of religious festivals: It is said that Devi Durga begins her journey from her husband's abode in Kailash to her paternal home on this day: The glory of Durga is known from the ancient treatise Durga Saptasati or the Chandi: It describes the incarnation of Devi Durga by the unification process of all the power of the Gods and her emergence as Mahisasuramardini in the eventual fight with Mahisasura: Recitation of these slokas is known as Chandi Path and has been recited and known to combat every kind of enmity and adversity, from ages forgotten: Since the early 1930s, homes in Bengal reverberate with the immortal verses from Chandi Kabya in the recorded voice of late Birendra Krishna Bhadra: It is a beautiful audio montage of recitation in the enthralling voice of Birendra Krishna Bhadra, Bengali devotional songs with narration scripted by Bani Kumar, classical music composed by Pankaj Kumar Mullick and a dash of acoustic melodrama: Script : Bani Kumar Music Director : Pankaj Kumar Mallick Narration & Chanting of Slokas - Birendra Krishna Bhadra Singers - Supreeti Ghosh, Dwijen Mukherjee, Sumitra Sen, Krishna Dasgupta, Pankaj Mallick, Utpala Sen, Sandhya Mukherjee, Pratima Mukherjee, Tarun Banerjee & Others

snippet.title: Roar of Narsimha Video Song  (Telugu) | Mahavatar Narsimha | Sam CS | Hombale Films
snippet.description:
Experience the divine power and fierce energy in Roar of Narsimha from the epic film Mahavatar Narsimha.

Composed by Sam CS and sung with intensity by Aniruddha Sastry, this powerful track features evocative lyrics by The Shloka and D. Mohan Kumar. Let the music awaken the inner spirit and strength of Narsimha within you.

Humare Avm Gana Channel mein Chhatishgarhi Hits Gana aap logo ke liye prastut karte hain. Hum Chahte hain ki har baar aapke pasand ka New Cg Song aap logo ko de. 
Hume apne comment me bataye Chhattisgarhi Geet kisake aawaz me sunana chahte avam video dekhana chahte hain. Hum Humare gana ko Dj Version mein bhi layenge, hum humare Avm Gana Me hit chhattisgarhi gana dene ke liye pratibaddh hain. 
Hum humare Chhattisgarhi geet ko badhava dene wale singer & actor Tijan bai, Usha Barle, Mamta Chandrakar, Anuj sharma, Nitin Dubey, Dilip shadangi, Alka Chandrakar, chaya Chandrakar, Bhupendra sahu, Mithilesh sahu, Kuleshwar tamrakar , Kavita Vaishanvi, Sunil Soni,
Kanchan joshi, Sarla Gandharw, Anupma mishra, Sunny pandey, Dilip Ray, Shashi Rangila, Virendra Chaturvedi, Shyam Kuteliya, Karan Chauhan, Kiran Chauhan, Monika Verma, Seema Kaushik, Gorelal Barman, Garima Diwakar, Dilip Lahariya, Devesh Dahariya
Mann Quereshi, Anikriti Chauhan, Amlesh Nagesh, isi tarah chhattisgarh ke hum sabhi any singer avam actor ko tahe dil se Dhanywaad Karte hain. Jo Humari Chhattisgarhi Boli ko Desh va Videsh me Badhava De Rahe Hain...
